====================================================================== 
1) Affected Software 

* Pulse CMS basic version 1.2.2

NOTE: Other versions may also be affected.

====================================================================== 
2) Severity 

Rating: Moderately critical
Impact: System access
        Manipulation of data
Where:  From remote

====================================================================== 
3) Vendor's Description of Software 

"Pulse is a simple CMS designed for small websites. It enables you to
take an existing site and add content management in five minutes."

Product Link:
http://pulsecms.com/

====================================================================== 
4) Description of Vulnerability

Secunia Research has discovered a vulnerability in Pulse CMS, which 
can be exploited by malicious users to compromise a vulnerable system.

Input passed via the "filename" and "block" parameters to view.php is
not properly sanitised before being used to write to a file. This can
be exploited to write arbitrary content to an arbitrary file via a
specially crafted POST request and allows executing arbitrary PHP
code.

Successful exploitation requires authentication.

====================================================================== 
5) Solution 

Update to version 1.2.3.

====================================================================== 
6) Time Table 
19/03/2010 - Vendor notified.
19/03/2010 - Vendor response.
24/03/2010 - Public disclosure.

====================================================================== 
7) Credits 

Discovered by Secunia Research.

====================================================================== 
8) References

The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) project has assigned 
CVE-2010-0988 for the vulnerability.

